    <descgrp type="add">
      <relatedmaterial>
        <head>Related Material</head>
        <p>The library also has a second Upjohn family collection, accumulated by a different line of the family, E. Gifford Upjohn. Valuable biographical and genealogical information will be found in the senior thesis written by Frederick Lawrence Redpath, entitled, "A String in the Fabric: The Story of the Upjohn Family" (Princeton University, April 1939). This volume is available at the Bentley Historical Library. In addition, there is a two volume history entitled <title render="italic">Upjohn; A Study in Ancestry</title> and <title render="italic">Upjohn; Two Early Journals</title> written by Richard Upjohn Light (1990) also available at the library.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
